    91	### Immutability rules
    92	
    93	- Base contract files (`spec.md`, `file_whitelist.txt`, `convention_version.txt`, `lint_config.txt`, `acceptance.md`, `eval_protocol.md`) are **NEVER edited** after lock creation.
    94	- Direct diff to any base file while `status == active` = hard stop. Checker refuses to advance stages.
    95	- Changes require: (a) amendment meeting → (b) new `<base_filename>.amendment.<N>.<ext>` with frontmatter `target`, `supersedes`, `meeting` → (c) lock's `amendments[]` appended → (d) `<base>.effective.<ext>` regenerated by checker.
    96	- **Whitelist changes** (both expansion AND shrinking) go via `file_whitelist.amendment.N.txt` amendment. No exception. "Shrink without meeting" is forbidden — mutating the locked hash, regardless of direction, breaks the immutability invariant.
    97	- `status` transitions: `close <round>` subcommand of `harness/check_operator_round.py` transitions to `closed` only if all Gate 1–5 pass. Operators may transition to `paused` or `escalated` via meeting; `aborted` only via human. Operators may NOT hand-edit `status` in the lock file.
    98	- `lint_config.txt` and `convention_version.txt` contain `<path>\n<sha256>`. Checker at Gate 5 recomputes the live SHA of the referenced path and compares — mismatch = blocker.
