   100	## §4. Challenge Section (anti-hallucination tripwire)
   101	
   102	Every meeting whose purpose is a **decision** (normative, design-affecting, or contract-changing) must include a Challenge Section with at least ONE of:
   103	
   104	- Concrete objection with reasoning
   105	- Named risk with mitigation or acceptance
   106	- Rejected alternative with why-not
   107	- Explicit uncertainty that was consciously deferred
   108	
   109	Meetings that are **purely factual** (verification, status check, evidence pointer) must state: **"No normative decision; verified facts only"** and list the evidence references.
   110	
   111	Forbidden: fake dissent (reviewer nitpicking to satisfy the rule). If the reviewer genuinely has no objection, the meeting is factual by definition — state that.
   112	
   113	Missing Challenge Section on a decision meeting = Gate 5 blocker.
   114	
   115	## §5. Gate Structure
   116	
   117	Gates 1–4 from v4 retained with enforcement clarified; Gate 5 added.
   118	
   119	| Gate | Name | Check | Blocker |
   120	|------|------|-------|---------|
   121	| 1 | Build & Test | `xcodegen generate && xcodebuild test` passes, test count ≥ baseline | Any failure |
   122	| 2 | 3-Evaluator Review | red_team + hig_guardian + visual_qa reports produced | Any evaluator missing or empty |
   123	| 3 | Cross-Agreement | 2+ evaluators agreeing on a file → required fix | Unresolved 2+ agreement |
   124	| 4 | Process Metrics | remediation cycles ≤ 2, BLOCKER recurrence = 0, brief accuracy ≥ 90%, SKILLS miss ≤ 5% | Any metric out of range |
   125	| 5 | Process Integrity | see §5.1 below | see §5.1 blockers |
   126	
   127	### §5.1 Gate 5 — Process Integrity
   128	
   129	Blockers (round cannot close):
   130	- Any commit in this round not traceable to a contract lock
   131	- Any edit to a base contract file (§3 immutability)
   132	- Any decision meeting without a Challenge Section
   133	- Any new operator/* file not registered in `FILE_INDEX.md`
   134	- Lock hash mismatch for any base contract file
   135	- Lint checker missing, failing, or unrunnable (`harness/check_operator_round.py` exit != 0)
   136	- Operator-layer drift audit reports contradictions (see §7)
   137	
   138	Advisories (noted in retro, do not block):
   139	- No new SKILLS.md entry — acceptable if retro explicitly classifies "no novel pattern"
   140	- FILE_INDEX line-count warning (between 250 and 300 lines)
   141	- SESSION_RESUME.md staleness > 48h
   142	
   143	## §6. Deadlock Escalation Ladder
   144	
   145	When two operators cannot converge in a meeting:
   146	
   147	1. **Reframe meeting** — each operator restates the OTHER'S position in their own words. Names the real decision axis. Frequently resolves miscommunication-based disputes.
   148	2. **Default-reversible rule** — if the dispute is low-impact and reversible, pick the option with smaller blast radius, easier rollback, or better auditability. Record both positions; implementer proceeds. No human, no Gemini.
   149	3. **Gemini advisory** — for **bounded technical disputes only** (lint rule choice, file layout, test strategy, refactor approach). Gemini provides ANALYSIS, not VERDICT. Claude/Codex still make the decision and record whether they accepted or rejected the advice.
   150	4. **Human escalation** — required for: product-impact, user-visible design direction, security/privacy policy, architecture change, irreversible migration, or unresolved operator deadlock after Gemini advisory.
   151	
   152	Timebox: 2 written counter-rounds OR 24 hours — whichever first — before moving to the next tier.
   153	
   154	Lock `status` transitions to `escalated` at Tier 4. Must record: both positions, tier path taken, what was asked of the human.
   155	
   156	## §7. Operator-Layer Drift Audit
   157	
   158	Runs at Gate 5 and after every operator-doc amendment. Implemented in `harness/check_operator_round.py` (section `audit_operator_layer`).
   159	
   160	Checks for:
   161	1. Role matrix consistency across OPERATOR/STAGE_CONTRACT/REGULATION — same agent, same stage, same role everywhere
   162	2. Stage names identical across all operator docs
   163	3. Every file mentioned in operator/* exists
   164	4. Every operator/*.md file (except CHANGELOG and meetings/*) is indexed in FILE_INDEX.md
   165	5. Line-count caps honored: AGENTS.md ≤80, .claude/CLAUDE.md ≤80, OPERATOR.md ≤120, FILE_INDEX.md ≤250
   166	6. No legacy doc cited at higher precedence than a v5 operator doc
   167	7. SESSION_RESUME.md last-updated timestamp < 48h (warn) / < 7d (block)
   168	8. `status: active` lock implies every stage_completed in the matrix was run through the expected performer + cross-validator pair
   169	
   170	Any contradiction → Gate 5 blocker. Resolution path: amendment meeting.
   171	
   172	## §8. Linter Enforcement
   173	
   174	- Config: `operator/lint_config.toml`
   175	- Runner: `harness/check_operator_round.py`
   176	- Enforcement owner: cross-validator of the stage, not the performer (performer may run it to catch own errors, but the stage-gate check is on the cross-validator)
   177	- Round 0 scope: **operator docs only** (filename patterns, line caps, required sections, frontmatter validity for meetings, index coverage). Swift linting intentionally out of scope for v5.0; revisit in retro.
   178	- Fail-closed: missing config, missing runner, or non-zero exit = Gate 5 blocker. No "best effort" pass.
   179	
   180	## §9. Context Discipline
   181	
   182	- **Always-read** per session: persona loader (`.claude/CLAUDE.md` or `AGENTS.md`), `OPERATOR.md`, `FILE_INDEX.md`, active lock if any.
   183	- **On-demand**: use `FILE_INDEX.md` to pick exact files. Targeted `ls`, `rg`, `git diff --name-only` permitted for verification.
   184	- **Forbidden**: undirected bulk-loading (e.g., reading every file in a directory to "build context"), citing legacy docs as authority (see §1), dumping full evaluation reports into meeting bodies (link + hash instead).
   185	- **Unindexed file opens** (opening a file not listed in FILE_INDEX): permitted, but log one line in `context_harness/blackboard.md` with reason. If the file should have been indexed, amend FILE_INDEX.
   186	
   187	## §10. SKILLS.md Update Protocol
   188	
   189	At round close retro:
   190	1. Classify: did this round reveal a durable pattern not already in SKILLS?
   191	2. If yes → append with S-number, name, pattern, example, why it matters. Mandatory.
   192	3. If no → state explicitly in retro: "no novel pattern identified". Gate 5 advisory, not blocker.
   193	
   194	Forbidden: synthesizing a "lesson" from a routine round just to satisfy the rule. Explicit opt-out is preferred to fake content.
   195	
   196	## §11. Amendment Protocol for This File
   197	
   198	Changes to `REGULATION.md` require:
   199	1. A meeting with `status: decided` and a Challenge Section (§4)
   200	2. CHANGELOG.md entry with date, summary, meeting pointer
   201	3. Version bump (v5.0 → v5.1 for substantive changes)
   202	4. Operator-layer drift audit re-run to confirm no new contradictions
