   206	## Appendix A — Terminology
   207	
   208	- **Operator** = one of the two top-level agents (Claude Code, Codex)
   209	- **Performer** = the agent producing an artifact in a given stage
   210	- **Cross-Validator** = the agent reviewing the Performer's artifact in that stage
   211	- **Round** = one execution of plan → design → code → eval → close, bounded by a single contract+lock
   212	- **Stage** = named phase within a round (see `STAGE_CONTRACT.md`)
   213	- **Meeting** = written, markdown exchange between operators with required frontmatter
