## Blockers (residual after v5.1)

- item 1: `context_harness/operator/REGULATION.md:3,196-202`; `context_harness/operator/STAGE_CONTRACT.md:3`; `context_harness/operator/OPERATOR.md:3`; `context_harness/operator/PROCESS_AUDIT_CHECKLIST.md:3`; `context_harness/operator/CHANGELOG.md:7-41`
  - What: residual doc/version drift. CHANGELOG records a v5.1 substantive amendment, and REG §11 requires a version bump for substantive changes, but the normative docs still say `Version: v5.0`.
  - Why: amendment/version metadata is part of the audit trail. A later operator cannot tell whether REGULATION/STAGE_CONTRACT are pre- or post-v5.1 without reading CHANGELOG. That weakens precedence and amendment traceability.
  - Classification: Blocker via REG §5.1 “operator-layer drift audit reports contradictions.”
  - Fix: bump affected normative doc headers to v5.1, at least REGULATION. Prefer REGULATION/STAGE_CONTRACT/OPERATOR/PROCESS_AUDIT_CHECKLIST all v5.1 if changed.
